SIMPLE: weedless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weedless
<hw>Weed"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Free from weeds or
noxious matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Free from weeds; -- said of a kind of motor-boat
propeller the blades of which curve backwardly, as respects the
direction of rotation, so that they draw through the water, and so do
not gather weeds with which they come in contact.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weed out</ent>⟦br⟧
